{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_83","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented FW-M7-003 in [synapse_mapping.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/synapse_mapping.py#L229): the repo now materializes deterministic per-root incoming/outgoing anchor maps, per-edge coupling bundles, and root-local coupling indexes from the local synapse registry. Surface roots map to coarse patch anchors, skeleton fallback maps to nearest SWC nodes, point fallback maps to deterministic lumped anchors, and each synapse side records query provenance, anchor type/resolution, distances, residuals, mapping status, quality status, and fallback or blocked reasons. Lookup helpers now cover inbound-root, outbound-root, and per-edge access without scanning the raw synapse table. [03_build_wave_assets.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/scripts/03_build_wave_assets.py#L276) now builds those artifacts during the normal asset pass and writes realized `coupling_bundle` metadata into the manifest instead of leaving placeholders.\n\nCoverage was added in [test_synapse_mapping.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_synapse_mapping.py#L34) for deterministic surface mapping plus skeleton, point, and blocked-coordinate cases, and the path-based integration assertions were updated in [test_config_paths.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_config_paths.py#L82). I also documented the shipped status and fallback semantics in [pipeline_notes.md](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/docs/pipeline_notes.md) and [coupling_bundle_design.md](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/docs/coupling_bundle_design.md).\n\nVerified with `.venv/bin/python -m unittest tests.test_synapse_mapping -v` and `make test` (53 tests passed)."}}
